  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening community media policies in the Pacific</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Pacific region has yet to grasp the essence of the concept &apos;media diversity and pluralism&apos; and its significance towards democratic and sustainable societies. 

This activity is a stepping stone to pave the way for community media to fully take flight and provide an avenue for the &apos;left behind&apos; to own, manage, and operate media where they receive, impart information and contribute to national development. Before this can be fully realized, this activity needs to begin with a review of existing policies on community media before bringing together community media stakeholders to discuss, inform the development of policy briefs that will eventually convince the development of community media policies in the Pacific.</narrative>
  </description>
